cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a visual technique for extracting subgraphs, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The technique is agnostic to the data abstraction, which suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and possibly also on machine learning (cs.SI) for creating adaptive data abstractions. The paper also mentions semantics and creating comprehensive abstractions, which could relate to natural language processing (cs.CL).
